I used to play this game all the time when I was a kid! It used to just be called "Commando" from what I remember. I used to go on forever in this game. Mobile controls are a little difficult to get used to compared to the original joystick controls because you tend to lose the center point. Also, weren't we able to hit the motorcycle guys up on the bridge with the grenades before? Overall, I'm pretty happy with this port. It's pretty faithful to the original, and that is what I was looking for most of all. I'm guessing that they won't update this game anymore, but if they did, Bluetooth controller support would be all that I would ask for. Well worth the $1.00.

It's decent compared to other games like this, and a good time waster.

Sound and music is perfect, graphics are perfect. Please give the uaer more options for control layouts.
